original: Elmquist, Einar Immanuel, kyrkoherde, Grimeton, f. 6/9/04 i Istorp, Älvsb. 1., av Emil E. o. Anna-Brita Elmquist. G. 36 m. Ave Hansson. Barn: Ulf f. 37, d. 37, Katarina 38, d. 39, Tord 40, Monica 45. — Stud:ex. i Lund 25, teol. fil. ex. 27, teol. kand. samt prakt. teol. prov 29, p*rästv. f. Gbgs stift 30. Var. v. kommin. i Ö. Frölunda, Grebbestad, Brastad, Tjärnö o. Veinge, v. pastor i Bokenäs o. Lindberg, past:adj. o. v. pastor i Eldsber-ga samt kommin. i Veinge, kyrkoh. i Grimeton o. Rolfstorp sed. 43.
translated: Elmquist, Einar Immanuel, vicar of Grimeton, born on September 6, 1904 in Istorp, Älvsborg County, son of Emil E. and Anna-Brita Elmquist. Married in 1936 to Ave Hansson and had children: Ulf (1937-1937), Katarina (1938-1939), Tord (1940), and Monica (1945). He completed his secondary education in Lund in 1925, received a Bachelor of Theology degree in 1927, passed his theological candidate examination and practical theological test in 1929, and was ordained in the Gothenburg Diocese in 1930. He worked as a deputy curate in Ö. Frölunda, Grebbestad, Brastad, Tjärnö, and Veinge, and as a vicar in Bokenäs and Lindberg, an assistant vicar and vicar in Eldsberga, and a curate in Veinge. Einar then became a vicar of Grimeton and Rolfstorp in 1943.
